blurb_text: The 2007 federal election was held on 24 November 2007. In Western Australia, the elected candidates were David Johnston (Liberal), Louise Pratt (Australian Labor Party), Alan Eggleston (Liberal), Mark Bishop (Australian Labor Party), Michaelia Cash (Liberal), and Scott Ludlam (The Greens).
